AU  - Diewert, W. E.
AU  - Turunen-Red, A. H.
AU  - Woodland, A. D.
T1  - Productivity- and Pareto-Improving Changes in Taxes and Tariffs
PY  - 1989
Y1  - 1989/04/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297457
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 56
IS  - 2
SP  - 199
EP  - 215
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The paper investigates the problem of tariff reform in a small open multi-household economy that only has tariffs and domestic commodity taxes as policy instruments. The concept of a productivity improvement in tariffs and taxes is introduced and conditions for its existence are established. We prove that a Pareto-improving change in tariffs and domestic taxes exists if a productivity-improving change in tariffs exists and if the Weymark condition on the matrix of household demands holds. Conditions are established for particular tariff reforms, such as proportional reductions and reductions of extreme rates, to yield Pareto improvements in welfare.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297457
ER  - 



