JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 56
IS  - 2
SP  - 235
EP  - 247
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper considers a small open economy with a safe sector and a risky sector. The probability of success in the risky activity differs across individuals, and is private information. It is shown that policies that sustain informationally constrained Pareto optima should not include tariffs. A laissez-faire competitive equilibrium, if it exists, is Pareto optimal. These results contrast with previous literature on the role of tariffs as insurance, where private risk markets are assumed away in an ad hoc manner.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297459
ER  - 



